Instructions to use makefile

To Compile and Run 'lab3.c' and also remove the executable, use command 'make'

make : This command will perform following activities
	1. Compile lab3.c and generate the executable file i.e lab3
	2. Run the executable lab3 (./lab3)
	3. Delete the executable lab3 (rm lab3)

To perform individual activities use following commands :

make ClrScr:
	This command will clear the screen

make Compile: 
	This command will only compile 'lab3.c' and generate the executable file i.e lab3

make Run : 
	This command will only Run the executable 'lab3' (./lab3)

make Clear : 
	This command will only Delete the executable 'lab3' (rm lab3)
